2.1. 8 CSO hubs - human rights (3) and democratization (5) – fully implemented their Capacity Development Plans, focusing on four capacities: i) financial sustainability, ii) democratic governance, iii) membership and volunteer management, iv) advocacy;
•	All 8 hubs rebooted their Boards, restructured management systems within organizations, developed and applied new governance and financial policies as well as strategic documents;
•	Annual budgets of 5 hubs increased approx. by 30%, 1 hub increased the budget by 3 times, 2 hubs increased budgets by 16 times;
•	4 hubs (Kherson, Rivne, Donetsk, and Chernihiv) managed to fundraise from sources other than international donor support (i.e. local business, local budgets, individual donations);
•	Sources from local fundraising are equal to 6% of hubs’ annual budgets;
•	Each hub implemented at least two advocacy campaigns in its region;
•	All 8 hubs prepared and published their annual reports. Donetsk and Kherson hubs became prize winners for their annual reports in the all-Ukrainian competition out of 25 organizations;
•	4 workshops on report writing, re-granting, democratic governance, advocacy, and gender mainstreaming were conducted to increase hubs’ capacities;
•	Largest national civil society development forum organized (1,300 participants).

